      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for being open to it. i mean, look at how much they've suppressed stuff in other areas like area 51 or even just certain government projects. if they found something massive on the moon—like something that didnt look natural at all—wouldn't it be easy for them to just pivot the narrative to \"it was just rocks and dust\" to keep everyone from panicking? i'm trying to find any mention of structural anomalies or weird light reflections in the raw telemetry data that might have been scrubbed from the final reports. any ideas on how to cross-reference the original mission logs with the stuff they actually released to the press?",
